description:
&lt;p&gt;The Acute Heart Failure Nursing service at University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire NHS Trust is a highly respected service, offering an outreach service with a high turn over of patients. We are currently offering a very exciting opportunity for a band 6 level experienced nurse to join our existing team. We are seeking a highly motivated, innovative nurse who is passionate in their delivery of high quality care aiming to improve the quality of life and longevity of patients with a confirmed diagnosis of Heart Failure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires the successful candidate, with specialist training and clinical supervision, to work towards an autonomous level within agreed clinical protocols/guidelines within the acute Heart Failure Nurse Outreach Service and outpatient setting. A background in Cardiology nursing is therefore a prerequisite for the acute Heart Failure Nurse role. In offering a collaborative approach, effective liaison with the wider multidisciplinary teams across all specialties within the trust and community services is imperative to this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameCath WatsonJob titleLead Acute Heart Failure Specialist NurseEmail addresscatherine.watson2@uhcw.nhs.ukTelephone number024 76965814&lt;/p&gt;
